Worried by the reported cases of kidnapping and murder in Enugu State over a period of time, the Inspector General of Police (IGP), Mr. Mohammed Adamu, has ordered the immediate posting of  Mr. Ahmad Abdulrahman, as the new Commissioner of Police in charge of the state. One of such tragic incidents, was the August 1 killing of a Catholic Priest, Rev. Fr. Paul Offu, along the Ihe-Agbudu road in Awgu Local Government Area of the state. Conveying the IGP’s directive in a statement on Tuesday, the Force Public Relations Officer (FPRO), Mr. Frank Mba, a Deputy Commissioner of Police, said  Abdulrahman will be taking over from CP Suleiman Balarabe, who has been redeployed to the Force Criminal Intelligence and Investigation Department (FCIID). “The Inspector-General of Police has ordered the immediate posting of CP Ahmad Abdulrahman to Enugu State Command as Commissioner of Police in charge of the state. He takes over from CP Suleiman Balarabe, who has been redeployed to the Force Intelligence Bureau, FCID, Abuja, as the CP in-charge of Intelligence. “CP Ahmad Abdulrahman holds double Masters Degrees – one in Criminal Justice and another in Conflict, Peace & Strategic Studies, both from the Kaduna State University. A graduate of Political Science & Administration from the University of Sokoto, CP Ahmad also holds a Post Graduate Certificate in Corruption Studies from the University of Hong Kong,” Mba said. According to him, until his recent posting, the new Enugu CP was the Commissioner of Police in charge of Intelligence at the FCID, Abuja. He has held many command positions across in Kaduna, Bayelsa and Ekiti Commands.